CMorseRunner Licensing Notice
=============================

CMorseRunner is a C++/Qt6 port of MorseRunner by Alex Shovkoplyas VE3NEA:
https://www.dxatlas.com/MorseRunner/

This repository contains source files that adapt logic, algorithms,
constants, and state-machine behavior from the original Delphi/Pascal
implementation, together with new files written for this port.

Upstream MPL Status
-------------------

The original MorseRunner Delphi/Pascal files used for this port carry the
standard MPL-2.0 notice and do not include the Exhibit B notice
("Incompatible With Secondary Licenses"). Under MPL-2.0 section 1.5,
that means the upstream Covered Software is not marked incompatible with
Secondary Licenses.

MPL-2.0 section 1.12 defines GNU GPL version 2.0 as a Secondary License.
MPL-2.0 section 3.3 therefore permits distribution of the adapted Covered
Software under GPL-2.0 as part of this larger combined work, while the
same files remain available under MPL-2.0.

License Allocation
------------------

The following files and directories contain Covered Software adapted from
the original MorseRunner source and are available under MPL-2.0 and,
when distributed as part of this larger work, additionally under
GPL-2.0 pursuant to MPL-2.0 section 3.3:

- src/audio/**
- src/core/**

The following files were written for this port and are distributed under
GPL-2.0-only:

- .gitignore
- CMakeLists.txt
- README.md
- src/main.cpp
- src/ui/**

Practical Effect
----------------

This repository may be distributed under GPL-2.0.

For files under src/audio/** and src/core/**, recipients may use,
modify, and redistribute them under either MPL-2.0 or GPL-2.0, subject
to the conditions of the chosen license.

For the GPL-2.0-only files listed above, recipients must comply with
GPL-2.0.

When redistributing this repository, preserve this notice and both full
license texts.

